gov.usgs.anss.edgemom

Class ReftekClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • gov.usgs.anss.edgethread.EdgeThread
        • gov.usgs.anss.edgemom.ReftekClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ManagerInterface, java.lang.Runnable

    public class ReftekClient
extends EdgeThread
implements ManagerInterface
    This client connects to a Reftek server, receives the data from that port and puts it into an edge database. It has the ability to expand if mixed sized packets are found. It will break 4k packets into 512 packets by default. 
    Switch   arg        Description
-h       host    The host ip address or DNS translatable name of the RTPS
-p       pppp    The port to connect to on the RTPD (def=2543)
-dbg             Debug output is desired
-noudpchan       Do not send results to the UdpChannel server for display in things like channel display
-nohydra         Do not send the resulting data to Hydra (usually used on test systems to avoid Hydra duplicates)
